name: dBase database file
comment: Probably file comes in conjunction with a shapefile and is one of three mandatory files used by the shapefile data format. It is used in the specification of the Esri shapefile format with the Esri ArcInfo geographic information system, where a DBF file serves as a storage for various geometrical shape attributes Format is dBase IV.

name: Polygon File Format, Stanford Triangle Format
comment: Two variants exist: pure ascii ply and more compact binary ply
